started: AL26Apr2019
last updated: AL09Jul2019

Summary

Prepare table for making VCF file for later use to select
variants overlapping with 1kg progect for joined PCA plot

Input and output data: 1,850 vars x 715 samples ( 519BC = 258UBC + 260CBC and 197NFE)

data_for_vcf.df <- data.frame(
  variants.df[,c("CHROM","POS","REF","ALT","QUAL")],
  ID=".", FILTER="PASS", 
  INFO=paste("SplitVarID",variants.df$SplitVarID,sep="="))

data_for_vcf.df <- data_for_vcf.df[,c("CHROM","POS","ID","REF","ALT","QUAL","FILTER","INFO")]
"#CHROM" -> colnames(data_for_vcf.df)[1]

data_for_vcf.df[1:5,]
##              #CHROM     POS ID REF ALT       QUAL FILTER                    INFO

## Var000000048      1 3677933  .   T   C  908688.24   PASS SplitVarID=Var000000048
## Var000000073      1 3680345  .   C   T   46177.02   PASS SplitVarID=Var000000073
## Var000000095      1 3683914  .   T   A   70072.62   PASS SplitVarID=Var000000095
## Var000000096      1 3683957  .   T   C     198.41   PASS SplitVarID=Var000000096
file_name <- paste(base_folder, "s01_ampliseq_nfe_1850_vars.txt", sep="/")

write.table(data_for_vcf.df, file=file_name, 
            quote = F, sep = "\t", row.names=F, col.names=T)
